						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Actually, from what I've seen, the Saturation technically *should* be "nesLuma[level][1] - nesLuma[level][0]" - the amplitude of the Chroma signal, which should THEN be scaled by userSaturationSetting.</div>That's just another way of describing things. nesChroma [level] = (nesLuma00 [level] - nesLuma0d [level])*0.5. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> Don't forget the 0.5. This is probably even better, because blargg's chroma [4] post still has the amplitudes scaled by 1.27, which was not right, as he said.</div>

