					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Using that formula, "pure red" ($x6) lies at 70.45 degrees (expected 90), "pure green" ($xA) lies at 207.72 degrees (expected 210), and "pure blue" ($x2) lies at 314.08 degrees (expected 330). These "pure colors" are based on the phases darkened by the 'color de-emphasis' bits (assuming that they were meant to be pure red, green, and blue).
<br />
<br />I suppose these differences are due to the fact that neither YIQ nor YUV seem to represent all of the colors in an "evenly spaced" manner (that, or the conversion matrices have subtle amounts of error in them).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
					
