				<span class="postdetails">
					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Sun Sep 19, 2004 10:59 pm<br /><b>Posts:</b> 1421
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">NewRisingSun wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The color emphasis bits attenuate based on the phases of $x4, $x8 and $xC, not 2, 6 and A, according to the NTSC Video wiki page, which has been reproduced in my algorithm as well.</div>
<br />
<br />Blue de-emphasis (bit 7) darkens phase 8 which, when applied to white, results in phase 2 (Blue) appearing.
<br />Green de-emphasis (bit 6) darkens phase 4 which emphasizes phase A (Green).
<br />Red de-emphasis (bit 5) darkens phase C which emphasizes phase 6 (Red).
<br />
<br />My calculations are based on the naive assumption that the color de-emphasis bits were meant to produce pure R/G/B when applied to white (with the proper hue adjustment) - clearly, this is not the case.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

