				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">NewRisingSun wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The NES does not produce "pure RGB", as said previously.</div>
<br />
<br />I never said that it did. I'm saying that it was presumably designed such that "red emphasis" was intended to produce a hue that resulted in pure red, that "green emphasis" would produce a pure green hue, and that "blue emphasis" would give a pure blue hue - in other words, based on the assumption that red, green, and blue were each exactly 120 degrees apart from each other, which is clearly <strong>not</strong> the case with YIQ and YUV decoding (in which red-&gt;yellow-&gt;green is 137.26 degrees, green-&gt;cyan-&gt;blue is 106.36 degrees, and blue-&gt;magenta-&gt;red is 116.38 degrees).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

